{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17645794","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17645794"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T20:21:40+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T20:21:40+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18133"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18133","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18133"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10847"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"78403"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10847","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10847"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18133"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"63765"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4931"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"25238"},{"type":"contributions","id":"25241"},{"type":"contributions","id":"26868"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"78403","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/78403"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EThe muscles in the anterior compartment of the forearm are arranged in three layers: superficial, intermediate and deep.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following muscles is part of the intermediate layer?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Flexor carpi radialis","Flexor digitorum profundus","Flexor digitorum superficialis","Palmaris longus","Pronator quadratus"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe anterior compartment of the forearm contains muscles responsible for flexion of the wrist and fingers. This compartment is divided into superficial, intermediate, and deep layers.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Eflexor digitorum superficialis\u003C/strong\u003E is the only muscle in the intermediate layer of the anterior compartment of the forearm. It is responsible for flexing the middle phalanges of the fingers.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EFlexor digitorum profundus\u003C/strong\u003E - This muscle is part of the deep layer and flexes the distal phalanges.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPronator quadratus\u003C/strong\u003E - This muscle is also part of the deep layer and is involved in pronation of the forearm.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EFlexor carpi radialis\u003C/strong\u003E - This muscle is part of the superficial layer and flexes the wrist.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPalmaris longus\u003C/strong\u003E - This muscle is also part of the superficial layer and assists in wrist flexion.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The flexor digitorum superficialis is part of the intermediate layer of the anterior compartment of the forearm.","The anterior compartment of the forearm is divided into superficial, intermediate, and deep layers.","The flexor digitorum profundus and pronator quadratus are part of the deep layer of the anterior compartment."],"references":["West, S. G. (2019). Anatomy and physiology of the musculoskeletal system. Rheumatology Secrets E-Book: Rheumatology Secrets E-Book, 17","Miniato MA, Anand P, Varacallo M. Anatomy, Shoulder and Upper Limb, Shoulder. 2023 Jul 24. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan\u2013. PMID: 30725618","Hutson, M., \u0026 Ward, A. (Eds.). (2015). Oxford textbook of musculoskeletal medicine. Oxford University Press","McCausland C, Sawyer E, Eovaldi BJ, Varacallo M. Anatomy, Shoulder and Upper Limb, Shoulder Muscles. 2023 Aug 8. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan\u2013. PMID: 30521257","Paulsen, F., \u0026 Waschke, J. (Eds.). (2023). Sobotta Atlas of Anatomy, Vol. 1, English/Latin: General Anatomy and Musculoskeletal System (Vol. 1). Elsevier Health Sciences"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"63765"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18133"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"63765","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/63765"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-10T16:15:26+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-10T16:16:05+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10847"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"78403"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt